      "comment": "SHIRALEE (7) has performed well as a hot favourite despite racing parked and working in her last two outings, winning from this barrier at Kilmore before a 1.5m second last week at Ballarat. Proven at this venue so can atone. ARE WEASLEY (12) had to race three wide without cover last start so prepared to forgive that result. Had finished top-three in five of his previous six outings and owns a storing record at this distance with two wins and two placings from five attempts. OUR BELLA LUCIA (8) is another that had to race wide and work last start but there was merit in her previous two efforts from this row. STAR RULER NZ (5) draws wider but gave a sight when he led and stuck on as runner-up at Cranbourne last time out.",
